in package1 create a POJO class to hold your input/output values
e.g:

    class Data {
        public String s;
        public int a1;
        public int a1;
    }

then you can change the signature of:

    public List&lt;Object&gt; returnvalue (String aString, int aInt, int bInt) 
to

    public Data returnValue(Data aData)

**UPDATE**

assuming you have 2 classes in package1

*Data.java:*

    package package1;
    
    public class Data {
        public String s;
        public int a1;
        public int a2;
    }

 and *Solution.java:*


    package package1;

    public class Solution {
        public Data returnValue(Data input) {
            Data data = new Data();
            data.s = input.s + &quot;append&quot;;
            data.a1 = input.a1 + 1;
            data.a2 = input.a2 + 2;
    
            return data;
        }
    }

you can use them in packate2 as follows *App.java*:

    package package2;
    
    import package1.Data;
    import package1.Solution;
    
    public class App {
        public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
            Data input = new Data();
    
            input.s = &quot;ipsum&quot;;
            input.a1 = 1;
            input.a2 = 2;
    
            Solution solution = new Solution();
            Data result = solution.returnValue(input);
    
            // use result
        }
    }

