answers.body_markdown:
In **ASP.NET Core 3.0**, `Entity Framework Core` and `Identity` related packages have been removed from the `Microsoft.AspNetCore.App` metapackage. So you have to add those packages separately.

Add the following `PackageReference`s to your project&#39;s `.csproj` file as follows:

&lt;ItemGroup&gt;

    &lt;PackageReference Include=&quot;Microsoft.AspNetCore.Diagnostics.EntityFrameworkCore&quot; Version=&quot;3.0.0&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;PackageReference Include=&quot;Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.EntityFrameworkCore&quot; Version=&quot;3.0.0&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;PackageReference Include=&quot;Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.UI&quot; Version=&quot;3.0.0&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;PackageReference Include=&quot;Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer&quot; Version=&quot;3.0.0&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;PackageReference Include=&quot;Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools&quot; Version=&quot;3.0.0&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;/ItemGroup&gt;

Now it will work!

For more details: [Assemblies removed from the ASP.NET Core shared framework][1]


  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/release-notes/aspnetcore-3.0?view=aspnetcore-3.0#assemblies-removed-from-the-aspnet-core-shared-framework

